OL,6,FWakefield Council voted in favour of a
OL,7,Fmaximum 2.99% rise in council tax,
OL,8,Fplus a further 2% increase in the
OL,9,Fadult social care levy.JSpending plans
OL,10,Fto plug a #33 million funding gap for
OL,11,Fthe next financial year were also
OL,12,Fapproved.JIn a statement Wakefield
OL,13,FCouncil said: "We understand that
OL,14,Fsetting the council budget in the
OL,15,Fcurrent economic climate is a
OL,16,Fdifficult and emotive subject for
OL,17,FCouncillors to debate.J"Regrettably,
OL,18,Femotions did spill over into the
OL,19,Fdebate and the meeting was adjourned
OL,20,Ffor a short time. All members of the
OL,21,Fchamber were reminded to debate the
OL,22,Fissues respectfully and when the
OL,23,Fmeeting resumed the budget was voted
OL,24,Fon and passed."
