OL,6,FIn a statement, Cllr Akbar told ITV
OL,7,FNews: "My use of the word 'scum' was
OL,8,Fto intended to describe the member as
OL,9,Fdishonourable.J"In the words of the
OL,10,Fdeputy leader of the Labour Party this
OL,11,Fparticular word is the "street
OL,12,Flanguage" of northern working-class
OL,13,Froots.JHe added: "I have since
OL,14,Freflected on the debate that ensued, I
OL,15,Facknowledge that my choice of words
OL,16,Fwas inappropriate and I apologise for
OL,17,Fmy language, I should have had a
OL,18,Fbetter choice of words and in future I
OL,19,Fwill ensure that I am more careful. I
OL,20,Fwill continue to speak my mind, stand
OL,21,Fup for the residents of Wakefield East
OL,22,Fand of course hold the Council to
OL,23,Faccount."
